subject: version-handler: add stat support
commitMessage:
version-handler: add stat support

Add stat support for both stat by session number and stat by blob name.

Both stat commands behave more or less identically with the exception
that stat by blobname is allowed for blobs that are not opened.
stat by session number is only possible for opened blobs.

The information returned is
blobstate:
  * open_read indicates that the blob was opened properly but makes no
  promises about the validity of the file data, NOT OK to read file now
  * committing - indicates that the blob was opened and that the OnOpen
  systemd trigger is running, NOT OK to read file now.
  * committed - indicates that the blob was opened and the OnOpen
  systemd trigger ran and succeeded, OK to read file now.
  * commit_error - indicates that the blob was opened but the OnOpen
  systemd trigger failed, NOT OK to read file.
size = <the size of the version file, is populated irrespective of the
state of the OnOpen systemd service>
The metadata included is meant for debugging purposes and reflects the
raw ActionStatus of the OnOpen and any future triggers.
metadatasize = 1
metadata[0] = the status of the onOpen systemd target
this is the same as ActionStatus
e.g 0 = running
    1 = success
    2 = failed
    3 = unknown

Signed-off-by: Jason Ling <jasonling@google.com>
Change-Id: I73823222ed69e1eded3587706e708a1d099d007b
